sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:description: PCinLacO is a promoter sequence that allows for combinatorial control over expression by CinR, which is activated by 3OHC14-ASL (positive regulation, C32m), and LacI, which is derepressed by IPTG (negative regulation, C1d or C63m). Effectively encodes the logic “CinR (and Cin AHL) and not LacI”, or, with both regulators present, “Cin AHL and IPTG”.
